HEADWORD: Croquette
<hw>Cro*quette"</hw> <pr>(kr?-k?t")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.,
fr. <ets>croquer</ets> to crunch.]</ety> <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>A
ball of minced meat, fowl, rice, vegetables, or other ingredients, often
in a thick white sauce, highly seasoned, breaded, and fried; <as>as, a
dish of crab <ex>croquettes</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
